# HSR (High-availability Seamless Redundancy, IEC 62439-3 Clause 5, ethertype 0x892F) carrying a GOOSE
# frame. Hand-crafted (no HSR device available): the outer Ethernet frame selects HSR via ethertype
# 0x892F, then a 6-byte HSR tag carries the ORIGINAL ethertype 0x88b8 (GOOSE), proving GOOSE dispatches
# over an HSR parent through the `etherType` field. The inner GOOSE APDU bytes are spliced verbatim from
# test/fixtures/packets/goose/baseline.hex (the bytes after that frame's 14-byte Ethernet header).
# Byte breakdown:
#   01154e000104        dst MAC (HSR-style multicast)
#   001122334455        src MAC
#   892f                outer EtherType = HSR
#   -- 6-byte HSR tag --
#   1099                Path (top 4 bits) = 0x1 (1), LSDUsize (low 12 bits) = 0x099 (153)
#   002a                SeqNr = 0x002a (42)
#   88b8                carried EtherType = GOOSE (drives inner dispatch → decodes as goose)
#   0001009100000000...  GOOSE payload (APPID/Length/reserved + goosePdu), taken from goose/baseline.hex
# Decodes as [eth, hsr, goose] and round-trips byte-perfect.

